    <div class = "row report-element report-section" id="HTML-section">
            <div class = "report-heading"><h4>HTML</h4></div>
        <div class = "report-text">
            <ul class="report-text-spacing">
                <li>Writing the HTML code for our website taught us the importance of correctly structuring and tagging HTML elements,
                otherwise the page and its corresponding style sheet quickly become difficult to format. This was a steep learning curve
                but by the end, we were both happy with our ability to create a nicely-formatted, readable website.</li>
                <li>The EJS framework was adopted to deliver pages using partials as templates (i.e. the head, header, and footer sections). Prior to
                this, the code was repeated for every page which wasn't sustainable, or good practice. Now that the website contains 12 unique pages,
                we're glad we switched to templates early in the development process.</li>
                <li>The Bootstrap 4 framework has been implemented, giving access to its wide range of pre-built components and allowing seamless,
                responsive web-pages to be created.</li>
                <li>Bootstrap also allows elements to reformat depending on the window size to accommodate mobile and desktop users. This can be seen
                 in the navigation bar, the <a href="/learnhome" class="report-text-link">Learn - Home</a> page, and across the website - when
                 the window is resized the web pages remain readable and aesthetic</li>
                <li>All pages are delivered using the XHTML standard.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class = "row report-element report-section" id="CSS-section">
        <div class = "report-heading">
            <h4>CSS</h4>
        </div>
        <div class = "report-text">
            <ul class="report-text-spacing">
                <li>CSS selectors were used to personalise the style of the website, taking advantage of the
                  id and class tags to customise certain elements. Structuring the style sheet quickly became important because of how
                  many different tags were required, and so a sensible order and naming convention was used to make style.css readable. </li>
                <li>The Bootstrap 4 framework provided a significant amount of styling tools, allowing pages to quickly look aesthetic and professional
                 with a single selector. These selectors were then modified to customise elements of the website and create a consistent style.</li>
                 <li>Styling for different browser sizes was considered, especially on the learn pages, using responsive images and the Bootstrap
                 row/column system.</li>
                 <li> SVG line animation was added to the title and logo using CSS code. </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class = "row report-element report-section" id="JS-section">
        <div class = "report-heading">
            <h4>JavaScript</h4>
        </div>
        <div class = "report-text">
            <ul class="report-text-spacing">
                <li>We spent considerable time writing a custom animation script (bubblesortanimation.js), adapting a quiz generation script which could be
                populated using the database, and several other customised animations to create a certain feel for the website.</li>
                <li>We have used the JavaScript anime.js and jQuery libraries for client-side animations, such as the section loading animation on this page.</li>
                <li>The JavaScript for each page has been separated to optimise loading time</li>
                <li>A custom login script was added for login/sign-up functionality on the navigation bar and the
                 login/sign-up pages. The input fields turn red when no information is entered, and key listeners were
                 added to allow form submission by pressing the Enter key, and to retrieve login/signup information</li>
                 <li>The JavaScript framework EJS (Embedded JavaScript) was used for page delivery and templating (see dynamic pages).</li>
                 <li>JavaScript is an area where we both feel we have learnt a considerable amount for both front and back-end applications,
                 especially given we had no previous experience using the language.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

