        <div class = "report-text">
            <ul class="report-text-spacing">
                <li>A lot of time was spent time learning Node.js and express to set up our own server,
                and several other modules were implemented to help achieve this, including password-hash, sqlite3
                and body-parser.</li>
                <li>Helmet.js was added to deal with URL validation. </li>
                <li>Began to set up a https server, however we were unable to get any further than self-certification. Unfortunately,
                when setting up remote hosting for our website, the self certification prevented this and so we had to remove it.</li>
                <li><a href="https://dashboard.heroku.com/" class="report-text-link">Heroku</a> was used to host
                 our website remotely - <a href="https://pacific-brook-65939.herokuapp.com/" class="report-text-link">Click here to view</a>.</li>
                <li>Login functionality was added which redirected the user back to the page they were on upon login,
                and if they accessed a page which required logging in, they were redirected to the login page. Password hashing
                was also implemented to protect user data</li>
            </ul>
