    <div class = "row report-element report-section" id="database-section">
        <div class = "report-heading">
            <h4>Database</h4>
        </div>
        <div class = "report-text">
            <ul class="report-text-spacing">
                <li>A server side SQLite3 database was setup, ready to use with dynamic pages and to store user information.
                A database schema was designed with constraints and foreign primary key interactions. The database was
                essential for our website as it populates the quiz information, leaderboards, account page information, and
                records and validates user logins.</li>
                <li>The database was also normalised, making it easy to query and insert/select data. This allowed
                more complicated queries to be completed, such as the joins required to display both the user data
                and their previous test attempts on the <a href = "/account" class="report-text-link">account page</a>.</li>
                <li>Checks were setup within the server to avoid SQL exceptions being flagged</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
