            <ul class="report-text-spacing">
                <li>The EJS framework was implemented to dynamically deliver information to pages, allowing us to create
                page templates for the constant elements such as the header and footer.</li>
                <li>Tables were dynamically filled with scores for both the test leaderboards, and for users to see their
                personal previous attempts</li>
                <li>We both gained experience with sending and parsing JSON for use in partials.</li>
                <li>The website layout dynamically changed based on if a user was logged in or not, specifically the
                icons available in the navigation bar.</li>
                <li>Dynamic page delivery allowed us to simply create one quiz.js script which could work for every test
                page, because the script determines which page it's currently on and populates each quiz with the correct
